I don’t really think the principle of explosions really fits this premise. The logic for it basically is if a statement and the exact inverse of that statement are both true then logically any other statement is also true. But I don’t see the exact opposite state being true in this. Just two similar states taking place. He doesn’t simultaneously exist and not exist like a Schrödinger’s cat analogy he just exists twice. Which would be two different P statements





